    <title>Severance season 1 is coming home on Blu-ray</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="A man in a gray suit sitting at his desk and typing on a computer in a cubicle." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/rx4XyxtYHRc3fR-B5AD0gcFGMfg=/0x0:6000x4000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73639472/Severance_Photo_010101.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Image: Apple&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="FNNA6a"&gt;While &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23268501/severance-season-2-trailer-date-apple-tv-plus"&gt;new episodes of &lt;em&gt;Severance&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;won’t stream on Apple TV Plus until January, you will be able to own a physical copy of &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23015650/severance-season-1-review-apple-tv-plus"&gt;the show’s first season&lt;/a&gt; in just a few weeks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="UCYEaE"&gt;Unlike Mark Scout (Adam Scott) and his fellow Lumon employees who can never entirely go home, &lt;em&gt;Severance&lt;/em&gt;’s first season will be making its way to more living rooms after its upcoming Blu-ray release on December 17th. &lt;a href="https://9to5mac.com/2024/10/08/severance-blu-ray-apple-tv/"&gt;As &lt;em&gt;9to5 Mac &lt;/em&gt;notes&lt;/a&gt;, the show is only being released as a Blu-ray at 1080p resolution and won’t be coming out in UHD. The release of the Blu-ray (which is available to &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.com/Severance-Season-One-Blu-ray/dp/B0DJC3GWYG?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;preorder on Amazon right now&lt;/a&gt;) is timed exactly a month ahead of &lt;em&gt;Severance&lt;/em&gt;’s season 2 return on January 17th, meaning you’ll have plenty of time to get caught up before new episodes start dropping. &lt;/p&gt;
